## Checklist

Please ensure your pull request adheres to the following guidelines:

### Quality Standards

- [ ] The course is genuinely awesome and you can personally recommend it
- [ ] The course is a university CS course
- [ ] The course has freely accessible materials (lectures, assignments, exams, etc.)
- [ ] The course is relatively unknown / non-hyped (not a popular MOOC or well-known course)
- [ ] All links are working and not redirecting to 404 pages

### Scope Requirements

- [ ] Course is **not** from:
  - [ ] MOOCs (Coursera, edX, Udacity, etc.)
  - [ ] MIT OCW (ocw.mit.edu) - submissions from ocw.mit.edu are out of scope

### Formatting Requirements

- [ ] Formatting follows existing entries in README.md (title â€“ description â€“ icons)
- [ ] Alphabetization is maintained within the category (ex. CSCE 48 should be listed after CS 240)
- [ ] Icons are correctly added (see [Legend](README.md#legend) for meanings)
- [ ] Sublinks (if any) point to different websites/domains than the main course link
- [ ] The link and description are clear and concise
